&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours: 15 per week; 7.5 hours Monday and Tuesday&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a professional, conscientious and highly effective person to join our friendly team as an IT administrator.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should be used to working in a fast-paced environment and have excellent people skills. Good knowledge of Systm One would be an advantage and general IT skills are essential&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Responsible for the IT functions pertaining to the day to day needs of the practice, in- house staff training and support in IT which will include liaison with outside agencies to ensure software is set up and maintained in line with the neds of the practice and any new equipment is functional in terms of IT software.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If we receive a high number of applications for this position, the advertisement may close early. You are advised to submit your application as early as possible to avoid missing your chance to apply.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information or an informal chat, please contact:&lt;br /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Julie Sampson or Lisa Jeffrey on 01332 755990&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you are a patient of this practice and you are successful, you will be required to register at another practice.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date Friday 6th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
